  id: 212,
  name: "Typing Mind",
  description: "Alternative user interface for ChatGPT with folders, search, prompt library, and advanced conversation management features.",
  fullDescription: "Typing Mind is a third-party interface for OpenAI's GPT models that enhances the ChatGPT experience with power-user features not available in the official OpenAI web interface. While ChatGPT is a capable conversational AI, its interface is deliberately simple—lacking organizational tools, prompt management, and customization options that heavy users need. Typing Mind fills these gaps while maintaining full compatibility with OpenAI's API (users bring their own API keys, paying OpenAI directly for usage rather than a separate subscription). Key features include conversation folders and subfolders for organizing chats by project, client, or topic; full-text search across all conversations (impossible in native ChatGPT); a library of saved prompts with variables for reusable templates; custom system prompts that persist across conversations; markdown and code highlighting for technical content; conversation tagging for metadata and filtering; export options (PDF, markdown, text, JSON); and keyboard shortcuts for efficient navigation. The 'prompt chaining' feature allows users to chain multiple AI calls together, using the output of one as input for another—automating multi-step workflows. Typing Mind also offers a 'compare mode' that runs the same prompt through multiple OpenAI models (GPT-4, GPT-3.5, etc.) side-by-side, helping users determine which model best suits each task. The interface supports file uploads (images, PDFs, Word documents, CSV) for analysis, with automatic text extraction. For developers and researchers, Typing Mind provides granular control over model parameters (temperature, top_p, frequency penalty, presence penalty) and token usage tracking with cost estimation. The platform includes team workspaces where members can share folders, prompts, and conversation templates. With over 1 million users, Typing Mind has become the preferred interface for ChatGPT power users who need organization, customization, and advanced features that make AI a professional-grade productivity tool rather than a casual chat application. While requiring comfort with OpenAI API billing (pay-as-you-go, typically pennies per conversation), Typing Mind offers capabilities that justify the minimal extra setup for heavy AI users.",
