  description: "AI customer feedback analysis platform that automatically categorizes, analyzes, and extracts insights from unstructured text.",
  fullDescription: "Eclipse AI is a customer feedback intelligence platform that solves a common problem for product and customer experience teams: having too much unstructured feedback and not enough time to analyze it. Companies collect feedback from multiple sources—support tickets, surveys, reviews, social media comments, sales calls, user interviews—but most of this data sits unanalyzed because manual coding of open-ended responses is prohibitively time-consuming. Eclipse AI uses natural language processing and machine learning to automatically categorize feedback into topics, detect sentiment and urgency, identify emerging trends, and surface the most impactful insights for action. The platform connects to over 20 data sources including Zendesk, Intercom, Gorgias, Trustpilot, Google Reviews, App Store reviews, social media, email, and survey tools. Once connected, Eclipse AI's models (customizable per business) classify each piece of feedback by topic (e.g., 'pricing,' 'bug report,' 'feature request,' 'customer support quality'), sentiment (positive/negative/neutral), and customer segment. The AI detects statistically significant changes in topic frequency, alerting teams when issues spike. For product teams, Eclipse AI generates a 'feature request prioritization' report showing which requested features correlate with high-value customers or repeat requests. For CX teams, the platform identifies recurring support issues that could be resolved with better documentation or product changes. The 'insights engine' highlights specific verbatim quotes that represent broader patterns, saving analysts from reading thousands of responses. Eclipse AI includes a dashboard with filters (time period, customer segment, product area) and export capabilities (CSV, PDF, Slack integration for weekly digests). Enterprise customers can train custom topic models specific to their domain. Companies using Eclipse AI report reducing feedback analysis time from weeks to hours, moving from reactive (responding to individual complaints) to proactive (identifying systemic issues before they affect many customers), and closing the loop on customer input—transforming feedback from a burden into a strategic asset for product roadmaps and customer retention.",
