  name: "Process AI",
  description: "AI platform that automates document processing, data extraction, and workflow routing for business operations.",
  fullDescription: "Process AI is an intelligent document processing (IDP) and workflow automation platform that extracts structured data from unstructured documents—invoices, receipts, contracts, forms, ID documents, reports—and routes that data into business systems. For organizations drowning in paper or digital documents that require manual data entry, Process AI automates 80-95% of document handling, dramatically reducing processing time and human error. The platform accepts documents via upload, email, scan, or API, then applies specialized AI models (trained for specific document types or custom-trained on your data) to extract key fields: for invoices, this includes vendor name, invoice number, date, line items, subtotal, tax, total; for contracts, this includes parties, effective date, renewal terms, termination clauses. Extracted data is validated against business rules (e.g., PO number must match an open PO in your ERP) and flagged for human review when confidence is low. Process AI then routes approved data to target systems: ERP (NetSuite, SAP, QuickBooks), CRM (Salesforce, HubSpot), accounting software (Xero), databases, or custom webhooks. The platform learns from human corrections—when a user corrects an extracted field, the model updates to avoid the same mistake. For organizations without dedicated automation teams, Process AI offers pre-built templates for common documents and drag-and-drop workflow builders. For enterprises, the platform provides on-premise deployment, SOC 2 compliance, and API access for custom integrations. Customers report reducing document processing time from 10-15 minutes per document to under 30 seconds, achieving 95%+ accuracy after initial training, and reallocating staff from data entry to higher-value work. For AP departments processing thousands of invoices monthly, the ROI is typically realized within 3-6 months through reduced labor costs and capture of early payment discounts (previously missed due to processing delays). Process AI represents a practical, immediately valuable application of AI that delivers measurable cost savings without requiring organizations to overhaul their existing systems or workflows.",
