  fullDescription: "LANDR (stylized as Landr) is the pioneering AI music mastering platform that democratized professional audio mastering—historically a $50-200 per track service requiring specialized engineers, treated rooms, and expensive hardware. Launched in 2014, LANDR's AI was trained on thousands of professionally mastered tracks across all genres, learning the sonic characteristics, EQ curves, compression settings, stereo widening, and loudness targets that distinguish professional masters from raw mixes. Musicians, producers, and podcasters upload their mix (WAV, AIFF, MP3, FLAC, M4A) and LANDR analyzes it, applying genre-specific mastering chains optimized for their particular track. The platform offers multiple mastering 'styles' (warm, balanced, open, punchy, bass-focused) and 'intensity' levels (subtle to aggressive). For streaming optimization, LANDR's AI matches target loudness for Spotify (-14 LUFS), Apple Music (-16 LUFS), YouTube, and SoundCloud, preventing the dynamic range compression that occurs when streaming platforms normalize overly loud masters. The platform includes reference matching: upload a reference track, and LANDR attempts to match its tonal balance and loudness while preserving the user's dynamics and arrangement. For advanced users, LANDR Studio provides a DAW-like interface with manual controls for EQ, compression, limiting, stereo widening, and harmonic excitation—with AI suggesting starting points. Additional features include distribution (upload mastered tracks to Spotify, Apple Music, Amazon, etc.), royalty-free samples and loops library, and plugin suite (EQ, compressor, reverb, delay). LANDR's technology is trusted by millions of artists, from bedroom producers to major labels (Sony, Universal have used LANDR for catalog mastering). While professional mastering engineers still offer superior results for critical listening (classical, jazz, audiophile recordings), LANDR delivers results indistinguishable from human masters for most pop, electronic, hip-hop, rock, and podcast content—at 1-5% of the cost, instantly, without scheduling, revisions, or per-track fees. For independent musicians, LANDR removes the final financial barrier between a finished recording and a release-ready, platform-optimized master.",
