  fullDescription: "Winston AI is a specialized detection platform that identifies AI-generated content (from ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Jasper, Copy.ai, etc.) and checks for plagiarism, serving educators, publishers, SEO professionals, and content managers who need to verify content authenticity. Unlike generic AI detectors with 60-80% accuracy, Winston AI claims 99.98% accuracy in lab testing, using proprietary models trained on millions of human and AI-written samples with continuous updates as new LLMs emerge. The platform offers multiple input methods: paste text, upload files (PDF, DOCX, TXT, images with OCR), or provide URLs. Results include an AI probability score (0-100%), sentence-level highlighting showing which portions appear AI-generated, and detailed reports showing writing patterns (perplexity and burstiness scores—key indicators of AI generation). The plagiarism checker scans against 60+ billion web pages and academic databases, producing similarity scores and source links. Winston AI is purpose-built for professional environments: team accounts with role-based permissions, batch processing, API access for automation (process hundreds of documents daily), and detailed PDF reports for audit trails or client delivery. The platform includes optical character recognition (OCR) for scanned documents—important for educators receiving handwritten assignments that were AI-generated elsewhere. Winston AI maintains a strict no-retention policy (deletes uploaded content after processing) and offers on-premise deployment for sensitive industries. For educators dealing with AI-assisted cheating, Winston AI provides a 'student submission portal' where students upload directly, with results logged by student ID. For publishers verifying freelance submissions, the platform detects both AI-generated content and content spun from existing sources. For SEO professionals avoiding Google penalties for AI-generated content (policy evolving, but historically penalized), Winston AI verifies content passes detection before publication. While no AI detector is 100% accurate (false positives and negatives exist, especially for non-native English writers), Winston AI is widely considered the most reliable option for professional use cases where accuracy matters—and where false accusations could damage relationships or careers.",
