  id: 241,
  name: "GitHub Copilot",
  description: "AI pair programmer that provides real-time code suggestions, completions, and conversational assistance within IDEs.",
  fullDescription: "GitHub Copilot is a transformative AI peer programming tool developed by GitHub in collaboration with OpenAI that helps developers write code faster, smarter, and with fewer errors [citation:5]. Unlike traditional code completion tools that suggest only the next few characters or line, Copilot understands context across entire files and projects, generating entire functions, boilerplate code, test cases, and even complex algorithms based on natural language comments or partial code. The platform operates within Visual Studio Code and other supported IDEs through two complementary extensions: GitHub Copilot provides inline coding suggestions as the developer types (completions, next edit predictions), while GitHub Copilot Chat offers conversational AI assistance where developers can ask questions, request explanations, or initiate multi-file edits [citation:5]. A key advancement is 'agent mode,' which performs autonomous multi-step coding tasks—handling compile and lint errors, monitoring terminal and test output, and iterating until tasks are complete without continuous developer oversight. For developers who prefer more control, 'edit mode' offers a conversational, step-by-step experience where Copilot applies edits directly to the codebase while the developer reviews changes in context [citation:5]. Copilot works across virtually all programming languages including Java, PHP, Python, JavaScript, Ruby, Go, C#, and C++, as the underlying models were trained on billions of lines of code from public repositories [citation:5]. Additional features include Copilot Edits for iterating on changes across multiple files using natural language, next edit suggestions (NES) that predict where and what the next logical code change will be, and customizable chat responses with custom instructions tailored to specific projects. Access requires an active subscription with free tier available, and GitHub maintains responsible privacy practices where user code snippets are not used as suggestions for other users [citation:5]. For professional developers, Copilot has been shown to increase productivity by 30-50%, reduce context switching (staying in editor instead of searching documentation), and accelerate learning for new languages or frameworks.",
