  description: "Health monitoring platform using AI and IoT sensors to detect health conditions and enable independent living for seniors.",
  fullDescription: "Caspar AI is a healthcare technology company founded in 2017 and headquartered in Palo Alto, California, that develops a passive monitoring platform for elder care and assisted living facilities [citation:7]. The company's solution combines artificial intelligence with Internet of Things (IoT) sensors to gather data on residents' health and behavior patterns, enabling early detection of incidents, diseases, and cognitive decline while supporting independent living for elderly and disabled individuals [citation:7]. Unlike traditional medical alert systems that require users to press a button when they need help (impossible if they've fallen and are unconscious), Caspar AI's passive monitoring works continuously without requiring any action from residents. The platform uses non-intrusive sensors placed throughout living spaces to track mobility patterns, daily routines, sleep quality, bathroom frequency, and other behavioral metrics. Machine learning algorithms establish baselines for each individual, then detect anomalies that might indicate emerging health issues—reduced activity levels could signal depression or physical decline, increased bathroom visits might suggest urinary tract infections, disrupted sleep patterns could indicate pain or cognitive changes. For caregivers and family members, Caspar AI provides actionable alerts and dashboards showing health trends over time, enabling earlier intervention before minor issues become medical emergencies. The company has raised approximately $12.2 million in funding from 24 investors including CABHI, Jolly VC, and angel investors, and has participated in accelerator programs [citation:7]. With 13 employees as of 2026, Caspar AI serves the growing market of senior care facilities and home care providers facing staffing shortages and increasing demand from aging populations [citation:7]. By enabling earlier detection and less intrusive monitoring, Caspar AI helps seniors age in place longer, reduces hospital readmissions, and gives families peace of mind about loved ones living alone.",
