  description: "AI social media manager that repurposes long-form content into dozens of platform-optimized posts automatically.",
  fullDescription: "Lately is an AI-powered social media platform that transforms long-form content—blog posts, podcasts, webinars, case studies, whitepapers, and videos—into dozens of short, platform-optimized social media posts. The platform's core insight is that most organizations produce far more long-form content than they promote on social media, leaving massive reach and engagement opportunities untapped. Lately's AI analyzes source content to identify key quotes, insights, statistics, and takeaways, then generates multiple social posts for each insight, tailoring messaging and formatting for each target platform (LinkedIn, Twitter/X, Facebook, Instagram). Unlike generic AI social tools that produce generic, template-style posts, Lately's models are trained on an organization's historical social performance, learning which phrases, formats, and topics generate engagement for that specific audience. The platform includes a content calendar for scheduling posts across platforms, analytics dashboards showing which repurposed content drives the most traffic and conversions, and team collaboration features for approval workflows. For agencies managing multiple clients, Lately provides white-label reporting and bulk content processing. The platform also offers 'evergreen' recycling, automatically resurfacing high-performing posts from months or years ago to extend content lifespan. For B2B marketers, Lately is particularly valuable for turning case studies and white papers into months of social proof. For media companies, it transforms articles into dozens of quote cards and headlines. Users report increasing social media output by 5-10x without increasing headcount, maintaining consistent brand voice across all posts, and seeing higher engagement rates from content that's been optimized based on historical performance data. By solving the content repurposing bottleneck, Lately enables organizations to maximize the ROI of their long-form content investments.",
