  fullDescription: "MPli is a comprehensive AI meeting platform that consolidates the entire meeting lifecycle—scheduling, conducting, transcribing, summarizing, and tracking action items—into a single, intelligent interface. Unlike fragmented workflows where teams use separate tools for calendar invites (Google Calendar), video conferencing (Zoom/Teams), note-taking (Notion/Evernote), and task tracking (Asana/Jira), MPli provides an end-to-end solution where AI handles the administrative overhead while humans focus on meaningful discussion. The platform begins with smart scheduling: AI analyzes participant calendars, suggests optimal times, sends invites, and automatically reschedules when conflicts arise. During meetings, MPli joins as an AI participant (optional visible or invisible) that produces real-time transcripts with speaker identification, timestamps, and keyword tagging. Post-meeting, the platform generates executive summaries highlighting key decisions, open questions, and discussed topics; extracts action items with AI-inferred assignees (based on who said 'I'll handle that' or 'can you send me...') and suggested deadlines; and automatically creates tasks in integrated project management tools. For recurring meetings (weekly standups, monthly reviews), MPli learns the format and can pre-populate agendas based on previous meetings' outstanding items. The platform includes sentiment analysis to flag meetings with unresolved tensions or disengaged participants, and engagement analytics showing speaking time distribution (helpful for ensuring inclusive participation). MPli integrates with Zoom, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, and Webex, plus project management tools including Asana, Trello, Jira, ClickUp, and Monday.com. For remote and hybrid teams suffering from meeting fatigue and information fragmentation, MPli ensures that no discussion is lost and every commitment is tracked, transforming meetings from time-consuming obligations into accountable decision-making forums.",
