  description: "AI assistant video editor that creates rough cuts, social media clips, and searchable transcripts from raw footage using natural language prompts.",
  fullDescription: "Eddie AI is an intelligent video editing assistant that transforms raw footage into polished edits using natural language prompts, eliminating hours of manual timeline scrubbing. Available as a desktop application for Mac and PC (with web-based limited features), Eddie imports videos from local storage, video editing applications (Adobe Premiere, DaVinci Resolve, Final Cut Pro), or cloud storage (frame.io, Google Drive) [citation:4]. The platform excels at processing footage with clear audio and dialogue—interviews, vlogs, podcasts, and talking-head content. Eddie's core feature is the 'Docs/Stringouts' mode, which allows users to import footage once and generate multiple different edits without re-uploading [citation:4]. Users prompt Eddie in natural language: 'Create a 1-minute cut from the interview,' 'Find the part where they talk about product roadmap,' or 'Cut together the discussion about company culture'—and Eddie locates the relevant moments and assembles them [citation:4]. After generating an edit, users can export as MP4, vertical MP4 (optimized for Instagram, TikTok, YouTube Shorts), or export the timeline directly back to professional editing applications (Premiere, Final Cut, DaVinci Resolve) for final polish [citation:4]. For video creators, editors, and marketing teams facing tight deadlines, Eddie reduces rough cut creation from hours to minutes. For social media managers, Eddie enables rapid repurposing of long-form content (interviews, webinars, podcasts) into dozens of short clips. For documentary and interview-based content, Eddie makes footage searchable and accessible—no more watching hours of footage to find that one perfect soundbite. The platform represents a paradigm shift from manual editing to AI-assisted editorial, where editors focus on creative decisions while Eddie handles the mechanical work of finding and assembling clips.",
