  id: 310,
  name: "Voice AI Wrapper",
  description: "Open-source framework for building LLM-based voice conversational applications with support for multiple ASR, LLM, and TTS providers.",
  fullDescription: "Voice AI Wrapper (Bolna) is an end-to-end open-source production framework for quickly building LLM-based voice-driven conversational applications [citation:6]. The platform orchestrates voice conversations using combinations of different Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR), Large Language Model (LLM), and Text-to-Speech (TTS) providers over WebSockets, enabling developers to create sophisticated voice agents without building the underlying infrastructure from scratch [citation:6]. Supported providers include telephony services like Twilio, Plivo, and Exotel for initiating phone calls; transcription services like Deepgram and Azure; LLMs including OpenAI, DeepSeek, Llama, Cohere, and Mistral for handling conversations; and TTS providers including AWS Polly, ElevenLabs, Deepgram, OpenAI, Azure, Cartesia, and Smallest [citation:6]. The framework includes a no-code UI playground at platform.bolna.ai built using the hosted APIs, enabling non-developers to test and configure voice agents without writing code [citation:6]. For developers building voice AI applications—customer support bots, appointment schedulers, lead qualification systems, or interactive voice response (IVR) systems—Voice AI Wrapper provides the orchestration layer that connects speech recognition, language understanding, and speech synthesis into a seamless conversation. The platform is particularly valuable for developers who want to avoid vendor lock-in with a single provider; instead, they can mix and match best-in-class components (Deepgram for transcription, GPT-4 for understanding, ElevenLabs for voice) and switch providers as needs change. As an open-source solution, Voice AI Wrapper offers complete transparency, customization options, and the ability to self-host for privacy-sensitive applications. The project represents the democratization of voice AI infrastructure, making sophisticated conversational agents accessible to developers who previously would have needed to build complex real-time systems from scratch.",
