  name: "Reelio",
  description: "Open-source video editing platform with AI-powered tools, marker systems for scene analysis, and advanced editing capabilities.",
  fullDescription: "Reelio (openreelio) is an open-source video editing platform that integrates AI-assisted features including advanced editing tools and a marker system for scene analysis [citation:5]. The platform is designed for professional editing workflows that require more than basic clip operations, offering extended editing tools such as ripple delete (delete clip and close gap), roll edit (adjust edit point between adjacent clips), slip edit (shift clip content within fixed boundaries), slide edit (move clip between neighbors preserving durations), insert edit (insert clip and push subsequent clips), overwrite edit (overwrite timeline region with clip), freeze frame, extract/lift operations (remove clip with or without gap closure), and comprehensive track management (add/remove/rename/reorder tracks, toggle mute/lock/visibility) [citation:5]. The marker system is a key AI-assisted feature that allows users to add and remove markers with color coding for AI-assisted scene analysis, supporting 10 named color presets, hex parsers, and color normalization functions that make markers AI-friendly [citation:5]. Higher-level compound operations include speed ramping (apply speed change to clip regions), reverse clip playback, duplicate clips, group/ungroup clips, and snap-to-playhead alignment. For developers and video professionals working on AI-integrated editing workflows, Reelio provides the infrastructure for AI agents to perform real editing tasks requested by users, with full undo support and IPC command dispatch. The platform's marker system is specifically designed for AI-assisted scene analysis, enabling automated detection and organization of video segments based on content characteristics. For post-production teams integrating AI into their workflows, Reelio represents an open-source foundation for building intelligent video editing tools where AI can identify scenes, suggest edits, and automate repetitive tasks while maintaining professional-grade editing capabilities [citation:5].",
