  description: "Chrome extension writing tool that helps users humanize AI text, adjust tone, and improve clarity across websites and apps.",
  fullDescription: "Phrasely is a Chrome extension writing tool designed to help users make their writing more natural and human-like while improving clarity and style [citation:8]. The tool rephrases sentences, adjusts tone, and refines text to better suit audience and context, whether for emails, documents, or social media posts. A primary use case is humanizing AI-generated text: AI detectors are often trained to recognize machine-generated content, and Phrasely helps adjust writing to sound more human and less likely to be flagged by these systems by rephrasing sentences and refining language to feel natural and personal [citation:8]. The extension supports over 50 languages, making it useful for anyone writing in multiple languages or creating content for global markets and multilingual audiences. Phrasely integrates directly with websites and apps users regularly use, including Google Docs, Gmail, and social media platforms, offering real-time suggestions as you write without interrupting workflow [citation:8]. With an average rating of 4.8 stars on the Chrome Web Store, Phrasely is trusted by writers, students, and professionals who value its simple design and helpful suggestions for clearer, more effective communication. The developer has disclosed that the extension does not collect or use personal data, does not sell information to third parties, and does not use data for purposes unrelated to the core functionality [citation:8]. For professionals and students who use AI writing assistants but need output that passes as human-written, Phrasely provides a lightweight, privacy-focused solution that works across the web without switching between applications. The tool is particularly valuable for those who write in multiple languages, need to adjust tone for different audiences (formal vs. casual), or want to ensure their AI-assisted writing sounds natural and engaging rather than robotic and detectable [citation:8].",
