  fullDescription: "Republiclabs is an AI research and engineering company focused on developing autonomous systems, multi-agent collaboration frameworks, and automation for scientific discovery. Based on emerging research in AI-augmented systems engineering, the platform integrates techniques like Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) with knowledge graphs to enable natural language interaction with complex system architectures [citation:7]. The platform's research direction includes automatic construction of knowledge graphs from unstructured engineering data, consolidating historically siloed information into accessible formats. This addresses challenges of data quality, integration, and interoperability by unifying engineering data into single knowledge graphs, partially automating model creation from unstructured data and mitigating skill barriers tied to ontology development and maintenance [citation:7]. The MBSE-Graph-RAG framework demonstrates how LLMs can assist in structuring unstructured data and support automated creation of system architectures, with natural-language querying mechanisms that reduce the expertise required to navigate and analyze complex systems. For engineers and researchers, Republiclabs provides infrastructure where users can ask questions in plain English and receive accurate, contextual information retrieval from system models—transforming traditional engineering workflows that required specialized syntax and deep expertise [citation:7]. The company's work has applications in model-based systems engineering (MBSE), autonomous agent coordination, and scientific discovery acceleration. For organizations dealing with complex, siloed engineering data—aerospace, automotive, defense, and advanced manufacturing—Republiclabs offers pathways to make that data accessible through conversational AI interfaces, reducing the time and expertise required to extract insights from technical documentation and system models.",
