  description: "Entity-based SEO platform that uses semantic analysis to optimize content, automate internal linking, and improve AI visibility.",
  fullDescription: "InLinks is a powerful entity-based SEO platform that goes beyond traditional keyword optimization to help websites structure content around entities, relationships, and topics—exactly how large language models understand information. As AI-generated answers become the new front page of the internet, traditional SEO tactics alone aren't enough; brands need to optimize not just for search engines but for language models like ChatGPT, Gemini, and Claude[citation:1]. InLinks addresses this need by functioning as a semantic optimization engine that transforms how search engines and AI models perceive your content[citation:1]. The platform's core technology identifies core entities your brand should be associated with—like 'entity SEO' or 'semantic search'—and analyzes content to determine entity salience, helping you add entities to titles, introductions, and schema markup while reducing noise from unrelated terms[citation:1]. This boosts your brand's prominence—a key factor in whether LLMs 'remember' you when generating answers[citation:1]. InLinks automatically creates internal links between semantically related pages, reinforcing topical authority and helping search engines understand site structure. It also generates schema markup for entities, making content machine-readable for both search engines and AI models, improving visibility in featured snippets, AI overviews, and LLM responses[citation:1]. For brands serious about AI visibility, tools like Waikay have shown that organizations using InLinks can increase their presence in LLM outputs by over 80% in just weeks[citation:1]. With its entity-first approach, InLinks prepares websites for the future of search where understanding relationships between concepts matters more than matching individual keywords.",
