  description: "Drone flight automation platform for DJI drones offering waypoint missions, live video streaming, thermal imaging, and real-time AI analytics.",
  fullDescription: "Mavic AI (AutoFly by Unleash live) is a professional drone flight automation platform that unlocks advanced capabilities for DJI drones including waypoint missions, secure real-time HD video streaming, thermal imaging support, and real-time AI analytics [citation:3]. The platform supports a wide range of DJI drones including Mavic Enterprise Dual Thermal, Mavic Pro Zoom, Mavic 2 Pro/ Zoom, Mavic 3 Enterprise, Mavic 3 Mini/Pro, Phantom 4 series, Inspire series, Matrice series, and Mavic Air [citation:3]. Key features include secure real-time HD live video streaming from drone to any global remote audience, secure thermal live streaming from thermal-capable drones (Mavic Enterprise Dual and Matrice series), advanced waypoint missions with timed interval image shots specifically designed for mapping missions, real-time telemetry and flight GPS logging for remote operations centers, automatic sync of flight logs with user accounts, and remote image and video capture with timed shots [citation:3]. The platform enables real-time AI analytics on live video streams through integration with Unleash live's cloud-based software platform, applying artificial intelligence to live video and imagery to deliver instant decision-making capabilities for field operations [citation:3]. For enterprise users, AutoFly supports secure remote account and drone authentication, remote navigation, media cloud sync, AI clipping, 2D and 3D modeling, mission planning, and real-time logging services [citation:3]. The platform offers a 14-day free trial and works as a companion app connecting drones in the field to remote operations centers. For professional drone operators in agriculture, construction, public safety, energy inspection, and surveying, Mavic AI transforms standard DJI drones into enterprise-grade mapping, inspection, and live-streaming tools, eliminating the need for expensive custom hardware or multiple software subscriptions.",
