  fullDescription: "Le Chat is Mistral AI's flagship conversational AI assistant, available for free, that combines powerful research capabilities, natural voice interaction, advanced image editing, and multilingual reasoning into a single intuitive interface [citation:9]. The platform's Deep Research (Preview) mode transforms Le Chat into a coordinated research assistant that can plan, clarify user needs, search for credible sources, and synthesize findings into structured, reference-backed reports on even the most complex topics—as though collaborating with a well-organized research partner [citation:9]. Voice Mode, powered by Mistral's new Voxtral model, enables natural, low-latency speech recognition that allows users to talk to Le Chat just like talking to a person, ideal for brainstorming ideas while walking, getting quick answers while running errands, or transcribing meetings [citation:9]. The platform is natively multilingual with reasoning capabilities, powered by the Magistral reasoning model, enabling thoughtful answers in multiple languages—from drafting a proposal in Spanish to clarifying a legal concept in Japanese to coding switching between languages mid-sentence [citation:9]. Projects feature allows users to organize related chats into context-rich folders, each with its own default Library that remembers which tools and settings are enabled, and supports file uploads and content pulling from Libraries to keep conversations, documents, and ideas in one place [citation:9]. Advanced image editing, developed in partnership with Black Forest Labs, enables users to create and then edit images with simple prompts like 'remove the object' or 'place me in another city'—the model transforms the scene while preserving characters and detail, making consistent edits across a series while keeping people, objects, and design elements recognizable [citation:9]. For researchers, students, professionals, and creative users seeking a free, capable AI assistant without subscription barriers, Le Chat offers enterprise-grade AI capabilities including deep research, voice interaction, reasoning, and image editing that rivals paid alternatives like ChatGPT Plus ($20/month) and Claude Pro ($20/month), all at no cost [citation:9].",
