  fullDescription: "Slides AI is a leading Google Slides AI add-on that generates complete presentation decks directly inside Google Slides, transforming topics, prompts, or imported documents into structured slide content in minutes [citation:10]. As the fastest way to get a coherent outline and slide bullets from a short brief, Slides AI is ideal for marketing overviews, internal briefings, lesson starters, and any scenario requiring rapid presentation creation [citation:10]. The add-on offers a free tier with limited usage and paid plans that expand credits, features (document uploads), and usage limits. Key capabilities include generating a slide deck from a topic, prompt, or imported text (DOCX, TXT, PDF) directly within Google Slides, plus rewriting and shortening tools to tighten slide text, and quick theme and layout adjustments [citation:10]. Output quality depends heavily on prompt specificity and input document structure—users are advised to use structured prompts specifying audience, topic, goal, tone, and desired slide types for best results [citation:10]. For best practices, experts recommend prompts like: 'Create a 10-slide deck for [Audience] on [Topic]. Goal: [Outcome]. Tone: [Tone]. Include 1 data slide with sources, a 3-step model, and an action plan' [citation:10]. While auto-generated layouts often need design polish and brand alignment, Slides AI dramatically reduces the time from blank slide to solid first draft, enabling presenters to focus on refining message and design rather than starting from zero [citation:10]. For business professionals, educators, students, and marketers who regularly create presentations in Google Slides, Slides AI replaces the tedious process of manually creating slide structures, writing bullet points, and organizing content hierarchies with AI-powered generation that delivers a working draft in seconds. The platform integrates natively with Google Workspace, installs from the Google Workspace Marketplace, and works within the familiar Google Slides interface [citation:10].",
