  name: "HIX Bypass",
  description: "AI text humanization tool that rewrites AI-generated content to bypass major AI detectors with multiple transformation modes.",
  fullDescription: "HIX Bypass is a specialized AI text humanization platform designed to rewrite machine-generated content so it reads naturally and bypasses leading AI detection tools including GPTZero, Originality.ai, Copyleaks, and Writer AI [citation:2]. The platform offers four distinct transformation modes—Fast, Balanced, Aggressive, and Latest—each providing different levels of text modification to suit various content types and detection evasion needs. The Fast mode delivers quick conversion with approximately 45% success rate across detectors, suitable for short, uncomplicated text. Balanced mode achieves about 65% success rate, offering moderate editing while preserving original meaning. Aggressive mode provides the most significant transformation, reportedly achieving 85% success on Copyleaks and 78% on Writer AI through deep restructuring of sentence structure and vocabulary [citation:2]. The Latest mode utilizes recent algorithm advancements for state-of-the-art humanization results. The platform's effectiveness varies by content type: shorter texts generally perform better than documents exceeding 1,000 words, and casual content like blog posts or social media text humanizes more effectively than formal academic writing with specialized terminology [citation:2]. HIX Bypass also includes SEO-friendly output and supports multiple languages. Pricing follows a tiered subscription model: Basic at $9.99-14.99/month (5,000 words), Pro at $14.99-29.99/month (50,000 words), and Unlimited at $49.99-59.99/month (no word limits), though users report challenges with subscription cancellation and unused credits not rolling over [citation:2]. For content creators, marketers, and professionals who use AI writing tools but need content that passes as human-written for academic, SEO, or publication requirements, HIX Bypass provides a dedicated solution with adjustable aggressiveness levels to balance detection evasion against output quality.",
