  fullDescription: "Short AI is an innovative video repurposing platform built with Google's Gemini LLM that automatically converts long-form video content into engaging short clips optimized for social media [citation:4]. Designed for content creators, marketers, and businesses with existing video libraries—such as podcasts, webinars, interviews, and presentations—Short AI analyzes video transcripts to identify the most compelling segments with high viral potential based on engagement metrics and audience interest patterns. The platform's process begins by feeding the video transcript to Gemini, which processes the content and generates a detailed JSON output highlighting sections most likely to capture and retain viewer attention [citation:4]. Beyond intelligent clip selection, Short AI includes automatic smart cropping technology that adjusts video framing to ensure the most important elements remain centered and optimized for visual appeal, particularly valuable when converting landscape-origin content to vertical formats for TikTok, Instagram Reels, and YouTube Shorts. The project was developed for the Google Gemini API Developer Competition, demonstrating practical applications of large language models in video content workflows [citation:4]. For creators producing long-form content (30-60+ minute podcasts, lectures, or interviews) who need to maintain consistent social media presence, Short AI transforms what was once hours of manual clip selection and editing into an automated process that identifies and extracts the best moments instantly. By combining Gemini's precision in identifying viral content with sophisticated auto-framing technology, Short AI streamlines the creation of high-quality, impactful short-form videos that stand out in crowded social feeds [citation:4].",
