  fullDescription: "Fireflies.ai (often referred to as Firefiles) is an AI-powered meeting assistant that automatically joins, records, transcribes, and summarizes conversations across major video conferencing platforms including Zoom, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, and Webex [citation:5]. The platform is designed for teams and individuals who want to capture meeting insights without manual note-taking, ensuring no important decisions, action items, or context is lost. Fireflies automatically joins scheduled meetings as a participant (with optional announcement), records the audio, generates searchable transcripts with speaker identification and timestamps, and produces AI-generated summaries highlighting key decisions, discussion topics, and action items. The platform includes a developer API (GraphQL-based) that allows integration with other tools—users can retrieve transcripts programmatically, webhook meeting data to external systems, and build custom workflows around meeting content [citation:5]. For organizations using FuseBase or similar platforms, Fireflies integration enables automated transcript retrieval and formatting for documentation purposes. Security features include API key authentication and encrypted data transmission. For remote and hybrid teams dealing with back-to-back meetings, Fireflies transforms meeting content from ephemeral conversation into searchable, shareable, actionable documentation. The platform is particularly valuable for sales teams tracking customer calls, product teams capturing requirements discussions, and managers needing to stay informed on projects without attending every meeting. Fireflies offers both free and paid tiers based on usage volume and features, with enterprise options for larger organizations requiring compliance and administrative controls.",
